  "notes": [
    "This phase intentionally removes migrated always-on attack/defense/skill/damage modifiers from Force talents when the source text requires activation, a target, Force Points, Force power suite state, item creation, or encounter/ally context.",
    "Primitive Block is wired into the existing ReactionEngine, analogous to Block/Deflect style attack-card reactions, but cumulative repeated-use penalties remain manual until reaction counters support scaling penalties.",
    "Greater Weapon Focus (Fira) is the only direct passive runtime rule added; it is limited by weapon text and melee attack context.",
    "Force Item/Talisman/Attune/Empower style talents are surfaced as action cards and explicitly not treated as passive bonuses on the actor because they require item creation/attunement state.",
    "Talent tree tags were normalized so scoped core Force trees carry force and scoped tradition trees carry force + force-tradition for future filtering/classification."
  ]
}
